Is there a trace in Servius Tullius ? Or in the other kings who have contributed so much that is excellent to the building—up of the State? Then even after the kings had been driven forth (and we note that such expulsion had itself been accomplished by the mind of Lucius Brutus and not by his tongue), do we not see how all that followed was full of planning 38 and empty of talking ?
